stories.description:
Add a power(int base, int exp) function to src/calc.cpp and src/calc.h. It should return base raised to the power of exp. Add a test case in tests/test_calc.cpp.

## EXACT FIX
1. In src/calc.h, add: int power(int base, int exp);
2. In src/calc.cpp, add: int power(int base, int exp) { int result = 1; for (int i = 0; i < exp; ++i) result *= base; return result; }
3. In tests/test_calc.cpp, add: assert(power(2, 3) == 8);
4. In src/main.cpp, add: std::cout << "2 ^ 3 = " << power(2, 3) << std::endl;
